
1 cup split chickpeas (chana dal)  (soaked in cold water 1 hr)
3 cups water
3 tomatoes, diced
1 Tbsp coconut oil
1/2 tsp cumin seeds
1/2 black mustard seeds
1 medium red onion, finely chopped
5 large garlic cloves, thinly sliced
1 tsp ground coriander seeds
3/4 tsp ground turmeric
1/4 tsp cayenne
1/4 cup minced cilantro
1 tsp salt


 1) Add lentils, salt, and 3 cups water to slow cooker.
 2) Cook on high 4-6 hours

 3) Heat oil on medium high heat.
 4) Cook cumin and mustard seeds 10-15 seconds.
 5) Add coriander, turmeric, cayenne, onion, tomato, garlic
 6) Stir 30 seconds, reduce heat to meidum low.
 7) Cook until onions are translucent and tomatoes break down

 8) Add onion/tomato/spice misture to slow cooker and stir.
 9) Top with cilantro and serve
